->$make_sorcery_translation_template <directory to sorcery sources>

->reply the asked questions

->it will create a directory (if none present) named "pot/language/LC_MESSAGES/" where langage
is the language in $LANG environement variable  (fr, us....)
in this directory you'll find cast.po, and other po files


->edit those files to add translation with you favorite editor (utf8 compatible prefered, 
else modify the first lines of the generated po [see getext info page for what encoding is supported]) 
or use poEdit (spell in creation)

->then run msgfmt <po file> this will create a mo file that you will put into 
/usr/share/locale/$locale/LC_MESSAGES/*.mo where locale is the language you replied

->test by doing an augur... if you see your translation then mail your pot directory to kyle after 
removing the *.mo files ^_^ (doing a find -name "*.mo" -exec rm {} \; )

note 1 : some editor when in utf8 mode add some MAGIC code at beginning of file, to remove this (this will cause msgfmt to abort at line 1:2)  run vi on the po and remove the unreadable char at beginning
